         <h1>Service and advice</h1>
<p><br>
Are you looking for a moving company but not sure what it can offer you? This article details for you all the moving services and the possible benefits, in order to facilitate your move into your new home. We offer here the average prices of the services offered by the movers with a description of each of these services.</p>
<h2>How much does a moving service cost?</h2>
<p><br>
A moving company will take care of the transport and delivery of all your belongings for you, but it also offers many other practical services to make your move easier to organize. However, not all moving companies offer the same level of moving service.</p>
<p>Rather than looking for packing and moving boxes, contacting the municipality, renting a freight elevator or looking for a temporary furniture storage, know that many movers offer these services often already included in the offer and the quote. move. The table below shows the average prices for standard moving services.</p>
<h3><br>
Compare quotes to benefit from a cheap moving service</h3>
<p><br>
With a wide range of services or options to choose from, you have the flexibility to make the move you want. opt for all the moving services included, if you prefer to take care of nothing, or just a few more essential options to help you transport your belongings. A moving company can offer you different solutions depending on your move and your budget! Take advantage of a service provided by professionals at an economical price by comparing several offers and quotes from movers. Take 1 minute to complete this quote request and receive up to 6 competitive offers from moving companies in your area by email! Simply enter your information and your move details to save up to 40% on the total cost of your move.</p>
<h2>What are the different services of movers?</h2>
<p><br>
Moving companies offer different services to meet the specificity of their activity. Indeed, a business transfer is not organized in the same way as a move of individuals. There are specialized moving companies to offer their services in certain sectors of activity which require very different skills and logistics. This is the case, in particular, for:</p>
<h2><strong>1- Individual moving</strong></h2>
<p><br>
Depending on the moving formula chosen, the movers simply take care of the transport and delivery of your goods, or can manage all aspects of your move. This service for private removals allows a lot of flexibility, in terms of transport optimization for example (group move or one-way truck) and the options or level of particular moving service you want, while guaranteeing a service and professional execution. Thanks to their expertise in moving, the transport and loading of your goods are handled quickly and in a completely secure manner. You also benefit from the movers insurance which covers your personal belongings.</p>
<h2><strong>2- Office relocation / Business transfer</strong></h2>
<p><br>
The moving professionals are also able to manage your office moving project. Intervening in several aspects such as assistance programs for the transfer of personnel, the restoration of furniture, the transfer of data in a secure manner, the transport of your professional machines and printers, as well as the removal of waste and bulky items , they ensure that the transfer of your business takes place in the best possible conditions. Organize the transfer of furniture, computer stations, equipment, files and personnel matters - while minimizing time and disruption for your business.</p>
<h3><strong>3- International moving</strong></h3>
<p><br>
Have you chosen to expatriate for a few years or for an indefinite period, or are you moving to another country for your work? Whatever your situation, there are specialized moving companies to take care of your move abroad. This service requires very specific expertise in order to coordinate the shipment of your personal effects to your country of destination and to assist you in all the administrative procedures required by your host country. The movers facilitate for you all the stages and the execution of your international move by offering you a service adapted to your needs and many moving services.</p>
<h3><strong>What are the moving services offered?</strong></h3>
<p><br>
The moving professionals offer a wide choice of moving services to meet all your needs. Your project is fully customizable according to the options you have chosen and the movers adapt to the specifics of your move. Below is a (non-exhaustive) list of the main services offered by moving companies and what they include:</p>
<p><br>
 Private move</p>
<p><br>
 Office relocation and business transfer</p>
<p><br>
 Moving of furniture and transport of furniture</p>
<p><br>
 International removals</p>
<p><br>
 Packaging services</p>
<p><br>
 Moving boxes</p>
<p><br>
 Special moves</p>
<p><br>
 Piano move</p>
<p><br>
 Cleaning</p>
<p><br>
 Disassembly / Reassembly</p>
<p><br>
 Handyman Services</p>
<p><br>
 Furniture storage</p>
<p><br>
 Insurance</p>
<p></p>
<p> Administrative formalities and procedures</p>
<h3>Furniture removal and furniture transport</h3>
<p><br>
Have you already packed everything and just need to transport some bulky furniture? Or have you just sold your sofa online and are looking for a carrier to ship it to the buyer? Whatever the situation, moving</p>
<p>companies have a perfect command of the techniques of packing and protecting your goods, guaranteeing the transport of your furniture without risk! Make moving your furniture as easy and efficient as possible!</p>
<h2>Packaging services</h2>
<p><br>
If you don&#39;t want to bother with organizing your move, leave the packing and boxing of all your belongings to the movers. You can also opt for a packing service for just a few items or for the &ldquo;fragile&rdquo; packing. This packing service by movers guarantees you adequate protection for all your items, in order to transport them safely without risk of damage or breakage during handling and transport. Otherwise, the movers are responsible for any deterioration due to poor packaging.</p>
<h2>Packing materials and moving boxes</h2>
<p><br>
Moving companies generally provide all packing materials and moving boxes free of charge as part of a particular move. However, you also have the option of purchasing these moving packing materials and boxes, either for your personal use or for the use of movers as part of their packing services. Depending on the company and the formula chosen, the cost of these materials may be included in the price and the moving estimate. To give you an idea, below is a table with the prices of packaging materials:</p>
<h2>Special moves</h2>
<p><br>
Sometimes there are special moving requests for the transport of fragile or valuable items, such as a fragile mirror, antiques, an old cabinet, paintings and other works of art. These objects require precise handling and specifically adapted protections, which are able to guarantee you professional movers and experienced in the transport of special moves.</p>
<h2>Moving a piano</h2>
<p><br>
One of the most common requests is when moving a piano. This operation is not only limited to moving and loading the piano, but also includes protecting the instrument and includes all the appropriate equipment to move it safely. Thus, a freight elevator may be necessary in this business, sometimes even a crane for a grand piano and depending on access to your accommodation. Your instrument is transported in a specific box and also covered by a mover&#39;s insurance at its real value.</p>
<h2>Cleaning</h2>
<p><br>
Among the options offered by moving companies, you can opt for cleaning your home. This may involve cleaning your old accommodation before it is put on sale, for example, or before returning it and recovering your deposit, but also your new home. This option is very useful if you need to organize your move quickly and have little time, or if you are moving abroad and cannot take care of it yourself. In addition, you benefit from a moving service that is both fast and professional results at a lower cost.</p>
<h2>Disassembly / assembly of furniture</h2>
<p><br>
For a quick move, but also for bulky or difficult to transport furniture, professional movers can dismantle all your furniture before packing and loading it into the moving van and assemble it once it arrives at the new destination.</p>
<h2>Handyman Services</h2>
<p><br>
If you need to install appliances or electrical appliances but don&#39;t have the time or knowledge for this stuff, some moving companies offer the services of a handyman, who will install and repair for you. any technical device or broken object. He can also take care of minor renovation work before you move in or in your old accommodation. This moving service is very convenient if your skills in small jobs and repairs are limited, but also because you do not need to worry about renting the necessary equipment or tools.</p>
<h2>Furniture storage</h2>
<p><br>
There may be a last minute problem preventing you from moving into your new place immediately. Or maybe you just want to put some furniture aside while you renovate your new home? Some moving companies have secure warehouses equipped with surveillance cameras. Here again, the movers take care of the transport and delivery of your goods to the storage area where they are stored safely, then delivery later to your new residence whenever you want.</p>
<h2>Insurance</h2>
<p><br>
All moving companies have insurance policies that cover your belongings during the execution of the moving contract and transport. This protects your belongings in the event of damage, loss and theft. Although most contracts include minimal, and sometimes free, movers&#39; insurance, coverage is limited. You often have the option of increasing this insurance to match the exact value of your property.</p>
<h2>Administrative formalities and procedures</h2>
<p><br>
Moving companies take care of certain formalities for you on moving day or can manage certain procedures that you delegate to them: apply for a parking permit or suspension from the town hall, pay the traffic congestion taxes , take care of removing bulky items following your move, have your energy contracts transferred, or, for international moves, pay customs clearance.</p>
<h2>Compare and save up to 40% for a cheap moving service!</h2>
<p><br>
Moving companies offer a wide range of services and are thus able to take care of any move or situation, in any circumstance. From simple transport without additional services, to a 100% managed move abroad, find the professional service that suits you best with a moving service that meets your needs. To help you make the right decision with a level of service that meets your budget, obtain quotes from several companies and find the offer with the best value for money. Send a quote request now - it&#39;s non-binding and completely free!</p>

